  "title": "Regional IT Manager",
  "description": "<p>Your main responsibilities include: -</p><p>• Providing operational support and enhancements for the SAP-ERP system across the ASEAN/India region.<br />• Leading the development, deployment, and continuous improvement of proprietary systems for use within the ASEAN/India region.<br />• Evaluating opportunities for system sharing with group companies in China and exploring collaborative initiatives across various IT domains.<br />• Communicating IT initiatives to senior management within the ASEAN/India group and managing the necessary approval and execution processes.<br />• Reporting regularly to stakeholders in the Japan HQ IT team and supporting the alignment of regional activities with group business strategies and long‑term plans.<br />• Delivering on-site support for diverse IT operations throughout the ASEAN/India region.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>· Bachelor's degree and above</p><p>· Candidate is required to communicate effectively in business and technical environments with Japanese speaking stakeholders, proficiency in business level Japanese is a must. </p><p>· Candidate must have at least 10 years of relevant working experience in managing and delivering IT projects with a global or multi-regional scope and proven experience overseeing the implementation of SAP systems, including S/4 HANA.</p><p>· Candidate with experience working in a diverse culture environment will have a distinct advantage.<br /><br />· Candidate with experience in implementation, enhancement and/or modification of internal business systems will have a distinct advantage.</p><p>· Candidate will be required to work independently under minimal supervision and a team player.</p><p>· Candidate with excellent communication, presentation, interpersonal and IT skills will have a distinct advantage.</p><p>· Candidate will be required to travel overseas for work purpose occasionally.</p>",
